id="post-1931" class="post-1931 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-direct-action category-good-fact tag-energy tag-home tag-money tag-saving"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2009/04/20/six-good-things-that-pay-for-themselves/" title="Permalink to Six Good Things That Pay for Themselves" rel="bookmark">Six Good Things That Pay for Themselves</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2009/04/20 12:49 pm"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2009/04/20/six-good-things-that-pay-for-themselves/" title="Six Good Things That Pay for Themselves" rel="bookmark">2009/04/20 12:49 pm</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Being a little greener and a little richer is really easy with these <a
href="http://www.brazencareerist.com/2009/04/15/6-things-you-can-buy-that-will-pay-for-themselves-in-a-year">six items that pay for themselves</a> within a year by helping the environment.</p><blockquote><p>5. Programmable Thermostat<br
/> Having a programmable thermostat is the easiest way to lower your heating and cooling costs. And having the house temperature right where you want it every hour of the day isn’t bad either. You can find programmable thermostats as cheap as $20 &#8211; at that price, it would probably pay for itself many times over in a year.</p></blockquote><div
class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-1111807-1931-5385354d5b590' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=1111807&amp;post_id=1931&amp;origin=www.thingsaregood.com&amp;obj_id=1111807-1931-5385354d5b590' data-name='like-post-frame-1111807-1931-5385354d5b590'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div
